st 60 people during a new attack in northern Cameroon in which some people were killed, police said. January 18, 2015 In "News" Chad's President Idriss Deby vowed Tuesday there would be no impunity for those who masterminded twin suicide bombings that killed 24 people and wounded more than 100 day earlier. June 16, 2015 In "News" Chadian President Idriss Deby on Wednesday vowed to "wipe out" Boko Haram and called on the group's chief Abubakar Shekau to give himself up, warning that he knew where the militant leader was hiding. March 4, 2015 In "News"